  "body": "**Is this a BUG REPORT or FEATURE REQUEST?**:\r\n\r\n> Uncomment only one, leave it on its own line: \r\n>\r\n/kind bug\r\n> /kind feature\r\n\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\nThe documentation claims that `ExternalNames` should be DNS names, but stricter RFC-1123 hostname validation is enforced.\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\nThe documentation should either specify that they need to be valid RFC-1123 hostnames, or the code should not reject valid DNS names.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\nCreate a `Service` with an `externalName` of `db_eu.example.com`, it throws the following error:\r\n\r\n```\r\nThe Service \"db-eu\" is invalid: spec.externalName: Invalid value: \"db_eu.example.com\": a DNS-1123 subdomain must consist of lower case alphanumeric characters, '-' or '.', and must start and end with an alphanumeric character (e.g. 'example.com', regex used for validation is '[a-z0-9]([-a-z0-9]*[a-z0-9])?(\\.[a-z0-9]([-a-z0-9]*[a-z0-9])?)*')\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`): 1.7.2",
